L&P Architects would like to invite passionate, motivate and creative candidates to join us for the following posts:

Senior Architectural Designer / Architectural Designer

Requirements:

Master / Bachelor in architecture or related major, have 3 - 6 years related solid experience, working experience in large architectural design practices is an advantage;
Creative and passionate in architecture design, and desire for growth;
Excellent communication skill and leading ability. Responsible for presentation and negotiation with clients, management of architectural design at all stages, including project early cooperation, coordination program, preliminary, construction drawing and design review;
Proficient in AutoCAD, Sketchup, Rhino, Grasshopper, Adobe Suite, and other professional software.
Fluency in spoken and written English is essential, Chinese (Mandarin) is a definite advantage. 

We offer 5-day work week, attractive remuneration and fringe benefits to the right candidate. Immediate availability would be preferable. Interested parties are invited to provide us full resume with expected salary and work portfolio .

*All data collected would be used for recruitment purpose only.

Reporting to the Associate Director (Estate Office), the Maintenance Manager is responsible for effective planning and managing the maintenance programmes to ensure themaintenance of buildings, structures, building services systems, specialised sports systems and equipment at the Fo Tan Main Campus and the off-site training venues are timely and properly carried out to assure they are in operational effectiveness to meet the needs, health and safety requirements of the company. The Maintenance Manager is also responsible for planning, implementing and monitoring additions & alterations (A&A) works of the company. Duties include:
Establish, manage and execute efficiently and cost effectively the maintenance strategies & programmes (routine, scheduled, preventive and statutory maintenance) to assure the operational effectiveness of all buildings, structures, building services systems, specialized sports systems and equipmentof the company;
Ensure full compliance of statutory requirements and regulation to ensure all facilities, venues, building service systems and equipment are operated under valid permits, certificates and licenses;
Provide technical advice to Management/users in respect of maintenance, A&A works and capital projects;
Collaborate effectively with internal users, consultants and external stakeholders of the HKSIL including Government departments on the maintenance works, A&A works, capital projects, and works conducted by third parties inside the HKSIL premises;
Prepare design, estimates, drawings & specifications, tender documentation for maintenance works and A&A works;
Prepare funding application and relevant reports/papers to Management/Board for maintenance works and A&A works;
Under the ambit of maintenance works and A&A works, coordinate and monitor the works tenders, services of contractors and consultants, manage contractor and consultant relationships; manage and review maintenance works and A&A works contracts to ensure all maintenance and users’ needs are being met with cost effectiveness;
Maintain updated Space Inventory and fixed asset of the company; 
Provide technical support and supervise the provision of Audio/ Video /Timing services for the company’s organized functions and events;
Supervise and manage a department of 30 staff members comprising professional staff and technicians;
Prepare annual maintenance plan, five-year maintenance plan and long term maintenance plan and to monitor the maintenance programmes progression against the plans;
Follow up and complete the outstanding works of the HKSI Redevelopment Project, including the settlement of final accounts, defects rectifications, and the construction of the Rowing Boat Launching Facilities, etc;
Perform any other appropriate duties as assigned by supervisor.
THE REQUIREMENTS

A university degree in Architecture / Building Services Engineering / Building Surveying or related disciplines with full membership of the HKIA / HKIE / HKIS or equivalent;
At least 10 years’ relevant working experience including building maintenance management;
Sound knowledge in Buildings Ordinance, regulations in relation to building and building services works;
Experience in managing a sizable team of professional staff and technicians;
Strong problem-solving and interpersonal skills;
Good command of both spoken and written English and Chinese; ability to speak Putonghua is a definite advantage; and
Proficiency in computer applications including MS-Office, Excel and AutoCAD. Knowledge in the application of Building Information Modelling (BIM) in facilities (FM) and asset management (AM) is an advantage. 
APPLICATIONS
Please send the completed application form with indication of your current and expected salary to The Human Resources Manager, Hong Kong Sports Institute Ltd, 25 Yuen Wo Road, Sha Tin, New Territories or email: hrdept @  hksi.org.hk on or before 30 January 2022. Please quote reference no. JD-20220117-MAM in the application.
Appointment will be on a fixed term contract. General information is available at the website http://www.hksi.org.hk.
Applicants who are not invited for interview within six months may consider their applications unsuccessful.
All applications will be treated in the strictest confidence. Data collected will be used for recruitment and other employment-related purposes only.
