About Rectrix 
Rectrix is specialist recruitment consultancy formed by a team of highly diligent recruiters with a proven track record in end-to-end delivery from mid to senior placements within the built environment industry.

About this Employer
A renowned property developer originated in Hong Kong with a vibrant working culture and excellent reputation in developing high-end residential and commercial property in Hong Kong. Upon recent land acquisition, the Group is going to further expand their project team for the upcoming premium project development in Hong Kong.

About this role 
Currently we are looking for a Senior Project Manager who has acquired full-spectrum project management to join their project development team in Hong Kong.  

As a Senior Project Manager , you will be responsible for managing large-scaled composite development projects in Hong Kong from initial stage to completion, including the coordination and integration of design planning, contract administration, technical activities, managing external consultants & contractors and moreover ensure projects will be delivered within standard quality, schedule and budget.

Ideally you will posses the following; 


Degree in Architecture or related background in real estate;
At least 15 years working in consultancy firms & preferably with past experiences in property developers; 
Registered Architect in Hong Kong with HKIA or equivalent;
Authorized Person (Architect) is a plus; 
Experienced in end-to-end project delivery of large-scaled residential & commercial development projects in Hong Kong.
Familiar with building ordinance, full-spectrum project delivery and well coordinate with consultants, main contractors and government officials;
Energetic, highly motivated, strive for excellence and high level of accountability;
Proficient in both written and spoken English and Chinese;
Based in Hong Kong for HK New-Built prestigious projects;
Less experienced candidate will be considered as a Project Manager; 

This is an unique opportunity to work for a renowned property developer that continually drives and offers the upward potential for strong career progression throughout the organisation.  

In return, the selected candidate will be offered a permanent position and receive a highly attractive salary package alongside market leading benefits with performance bonus. If you are interested in this position, please send your updated resume to info @ rectrix-group.com

THE JOB 

Reporting to the Project Manager (Estate Office), the Assistant Project Manager (Estate Office) will assist in the planning, coordination and supervision of the new Facilities Development Project. His/Her responsibilities include the followings:

Coordination with stakeholders on the technical requirements of the Facilities Development Project;
Liaison with Government bodies for approval on project funding and project requirements;
Management of consultants and contractors on project implementation;
Aligning with the Facilities Department and the Maintenance Department on the current/future facilities operation mode;
Preparation of design drawings, detail drawings and tender document in connection with the project;
Co-ordination and supervision of the project to ensure that it is properly implemented and recorded in accordance with the agreed programme and budget, quantity and quality standards, as well as the relevant statutory requirements;
Documentation and reporting of the project status to the project committees, HKSIL management, Board of Directors of HKSIL and the relevant Government bodies; and
To perform any other appropriate duties as assigned by supervisor.


THE REQUIREMENTS


Possess a university degree in Architecture / Building Construction Management / Building Engineering / Electrical and Mechanical Engineering / Quantity Surveying or related disciplines, preferably with a relevant professional qualification;
At least 6 years’ relevant local experience in project management of building projects and refurbishment projects. Experience in Government or Government subvention projects, BEAM, Building Information Modeling and Modular Integrated Construction would be an advantage;
Excellent command of both spoken and written English and Chinese with strong interpersonal skills;
Highly motivated with strong sense of responsibility, able to work collaboratively and independently; and
Proficiency in computer applications including MS-Office and AutoCAD.


APPLICATIONS

Please send the completed Application Form with indication of expected salary to The Human Resources Manager, Hong Kong Sports Institute Ltd, 25 Yuen Wo Road, Sha Tin, New Territories or email: hrdept @ hksi.org.hk on or before 25 January 2022. Please quote reference no. JD-20220112-APM in the application.

